The purpose of this Technical Note is to describe the details of endoscopically assisted resection of intramuscular lipoma of the soleus. Patient is in supine position with the legs spread. Endoscopically assisted resection of intramuscular lipoma of the soleus of the left leg. This procedure is performed with the proximal medial portal and the distal medial portal. The distal medial portal is the viewing portal, and the proximal medial portal is the working portal. The tumor is slowly freed from the soleus muscle by finger dissection (Fig 5).Fig 5Endoscopically assisted resection of intramuscular lipoma of the soleus of the left leg.